{% section #step-6 step=6 title="Handle POST Request" %}
Now after serving the HTML page, add methods necessary to integrate with the OpenAI AI.

First, import `openai` at the top of the `main.js` file and add bunch of Appwrite helper functions:

```js
import { OpenAIApi, Configuration } from 'openai';
```

Next add code to validate the body of the request and initialise the Appwrite SDK:
```js
const client = new Client()
  .setEndpoint(process.env.APPWRITE_ENDPOINT || "https://cloud.appwrite.io/v1")
  .setProject(process.env.APPWRITE_FUNCTION_PROJECT_ID)
  .setKey(process.env.APPWRITE_API_KEY);

if (!req.body.prompt && typeof req.body.prompt !== "string") {
  return res.json({ ok: false, error: "Prompt is required" }, 400);
}

const openai = new OpenAIApi(
  new Configuration({
    apiKey: process.env.OPENAI_API_KEY,
  })
);
```

Finally, Make a request to the OpenAI API and return the response:

```js
try {
  const response = await openai.createChatCompletion({
    model: 'gpt-3.5-turbo',
    max_tokens: parseInt(process.env.OPENAI_MAX_TOKENS ?? '512'),
    messages: [{ role: 'user', content: req.body.prompt }],
  });
  const completion = response.data.choices[0].message?.content;
  return res.json({ ok: true, completion }, 200);
} catch (err) {
  return res.json({ ok: false, error: 'Failed to query model.' }, 500);
}
```
{% /section %}

